379
00:36:44.289 --> 00:36:45.768
who were the leaders of

380
00:36:45.812 --> 00:36:48.423
the Citizens Against
Toxic Spray movement.

381
00:36:48.467 --> 00:36:49.946
- This is for Sadie.

382
00:36:51.818 --> 00:36:54.516
The car was parked here but
they were walking up here

383
00:36:54.560 --> 00:36:58.868
with all their gear. obviously
thinking I wasn't home.

384
00:37:00.305 --> 00:37:02.481
He didn't really explain
why they were here.

385
00:37:02.524 --> 00:37:04.613
It was when I
realized the other guy

386
00:37:04.657 --> 00:37:07.312
was sneaking up there
and talking to the kids.

387
00:37:07.355 --> 00:37:08.748
then I got kind of angry.

388
00:37:10.228 --> 00:37:12.491
He was asking them
all about what kinds

389
00:37:12.534 --> 00:37:17.539
of deformed critters we had in
the freezer--because we did!

390
00:37:19.019 --> 00:37:20.586
We saved a bunch of
them hoping to get 'em

391
00:37:20.629 --> 00:37:23.284
analyzed to see what was in 'em.

392
00:37:23.328 --> 00:37:26.244
- But the rear door flew open
as it drove away and they

393
00:37:26.287 --> 00:37:29.595
could see that there were
large video cameras in there.

394
00:37:31.336 --> 00:37:33.120
- [Carol] The phone company
itself. their employees

395
00:37:33.163 --> 00:37:36.210
told us that our phones
were being tapped.

396
00:37:38.691 --> 00:37:40.432
Steve would get in the car

397
00:37:40.475 --> 00:37:42.390
and he would usually
drive over the back roads.

398
00:37:42.434 --> 00:37:45.393
Nobody drives over
there. nobody did then.

399
00:37:46.873 --> 00:37:48.440
Suddenly. there'd
be a car behind him

400
00:37:48.483 --> 00:37:51.486
and it would stick
to him all the way

401
00:37:51.530 --> 00:37:56.012
every time they went to
the valley to do anything.

402
00:37:56.056 --> 00:37:57.753
Who is it? We don't know.

403
00:37:57.797 --> 00:38:01.322
Is it government people?
Is it industry people?

404
00:38:01.366 --> 00:38:03.846
There was no way to really know.

405
00:38:05.674 --> 00:38:07.459
- [Bruce] It was an obvious
attempt to try to intimidate

406
00:38:07.502 --> 00:38:10.984
the folks who were
bringing this litigation

407
00:38:11.027 --> 00:38:13.987
to try to reduce
herbicide aerial spraying.

408
00:38:20.950 --> 00:38:24.476
- Well. we won a
temporary injunction.

409
00:38:28.654 --> 00:38:30.699
What the Judge in the CATS case.

410
00:38:30.743 --> 00:38:33.398
thanks to all those
scientists and studies

411
00:38:33.441 --> 00:38:37.619
that we were able to
compile. ruled was that hey.

412
00:38:37.663 --> 00:38:41.623
you've got to include in
your environmental impact

413
00:38:41.667 --> 00:38:45.410
statement the effects of
these chemicals in Vietnam.

414
00:38:47.150 --> 00:38:51.198
And that was a blow to the
Forest Service because by then.

415
00:38:51.241 --> 00:38:56.246
there were some really
documented impacts in Vietnam.

416
00:39:03.558 --> 00:39:05.778
We felt vindicated
in a lot of ways

417
00:39:05.821 --> 00:39:10.217
but his injunction only
applied to 2.4.5-T.

418
00:39:10.260 --> 00:39:12.088
which was half of Agent Orange.

419
00:39:20.749 --> 00:39:24.144
The CATS case generated
quite a bit of publicity

420
00:39:25.841 --> 00:39:29.715
just because it was so amazing
that these people living

421
00:39:29.758 --> 00:39:33.240
out in the woods could sue the
Federal government and win.

422
00:39:33.283 --> 00:39:36.896
It was kind of unheard
of at that point.

423
00:39:36.939 --> 00:39:38.985
especially on an
environmental issue.

424
00:39:40.769 --> 00:39:44.164
So other people
were contacting us.

425
00:39:44.207 --> 00:39:47.254
They were all experiencing
the same thing.

426
00:39:47.297 --> 00:39:51.258
This was people in other
places in Oregon. in

427
00:39:51.301 --> 00:39:55.915
the state of Washington. in
Idaho. in Northern California.

428
00:39:55.958 --> 00:39:59.484
There were even requests
from places back east.

429
00:40:01.311 --> 00:40:03.096
- [Susan] One thing I'll
never forget is that just

430
00:40:03.139 --> 00:40:06.795
gathering scientific data
from Oregon State University.

431
00:40:06.839 --> 00:40:09.885
what we were able to find
from their own library.

